    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
        <body>
            <div xml:id="KT387-kilavi">
                <p type="edition">piriviṭai vaṟpuṟuttun tōḻikkuk kiḻatti vaṉpoṟaiyetir aḻintatu. </p>


                <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken when being desolate in the face of
                    encouragement by HER to the confidante, who encourages [her] in the time of
                    separation. </p>
            </div>

            <div xml:id="KT387">
                <lg type="edition">
                    <l> ellai kaḻiya mullai malarak</l>
                    <l> katirciṉan taṇinta kaiyaṟu mālaiyu</l>
                    <l> miravaram pāka nīntiṉa māyi</l>
                    <l> ṉevaṉkol vāḻi tōḻi</l>
                    <l> kaṅkul veḷḷaṅ kaṭaliṉum peritē.</l>


                </lg>

                <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <l rend="indent"> And if we were to swim the border of night ,</l>
                    <l rend="indent2"> evening, when action subsides, as the beams' anger decreases,</l>
                    <l rend="indent3"> while daylight passes [and] the jasmine blossoms,</l>
                    <l> what [of that], oh friend?</l>
                    <l> The flood of night [is] greater than the sea.</l>


                </lg>
            </div>
        </body>
